Dynamically calls a user defined procedure. call_proc(_myProc, 'var1') is the equivalent of _myProc('var1'), except you could dynamically build the procedure name if need be. This is useful for dynamic coding, however, closures work best for callbacks. Throws an InvalidProcedureException if the procedure isn't defined. If you are hardcoding the first parameter, a warning will be issued, because it is much more efficient and safe to directly use a procedure if you know what its name is beforehand.
